<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-01-07T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-01-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/4293: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-07T13:00:00+00:00">January 7, 1937—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Another contingent of about 4000 Italians arrived in Cadiz last week thus
                            making total of approximately 8000 arrivals during the past fortnight
                            exclusive of the Red Cross unit mentioned in my telegram December 30, 1
                                p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d118fn3"><ref target="frus1936v02#pg_620"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1936, Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 620</ref>.</note> These forces
                            are for the most part infantrymen and artillerymen and are said to have
                            come directly from Abyssinia. Cruiser <hi rend="italic">Baleares</hi>
                            sister ship of Cruiser <hi rend="italic">Canarias</hi>, recently
                            launched, is now being equipped in Cadiz with guns and will be ready for
                            service within a week.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>